### Description

I updated a component in my project to use `@for` `track` function.
And it logged a bunch of errors on the backend.

Here is a simple example modified from the component and [an online example `trackCourse`](https://blog.angular-university.io/angular-for/)

```ts
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';
import { AfterViewInit, Component, ElementRef, OnDestroy, OnInit, ViewChild } from '@angular/core';
import { ResizeObserver } from '@juggle/resize-observer';


@Component({
  selector: 'app-courses',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [
    CommonModule,
  ],
  template: `<div #element>
    <div>
      <ul>
        @for (course of courses; track trackCourse) {
        <li>{{ course }}</li>
        }
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>`,
})
